Let's learn ABCD the fashion way - Part 3!📚👗
I for Ikat Kurta - A dyeing technique in which the threads are tie-dyed before weaving. A perfectly traditional print for simple festive occasions.
J for Jacquard Skirt - A complex pattern that is woven directly on the garment. A perfect wardrobe staple for for an OTT yet elegant look.
K for Kilt Skirt - A woven pleated knee-length skirt that is traditional to the men in the Scottish Highlands. Chic & versatile.
L for Loafers - An easy slip on shoe without laces that is perfect for semi-formal occasions.
Did you like our version of ABCD?
